* DEVICE BASIC SECURITY CONFIGURATION

- Enable an unencrypted password

  SW1>en
  SW1#conf t
  Enter configuration commands, one per line.  End with CNTL/Z.
  SW1(config)#hostname SW1
  SW1(config)#enable password CCNA
  SW1(config)#exit

- Show the active configuration file on the device
  SW1#show running-config
- Alternative way to enable password(Ensure that the current and future passwords are encrypted but can be easily cracked)
  SW1#conf t
  Enter configuration commands, one per line.  End with CNTL/Z.
  SW1(config)#service password-encryption
- HOW TO CONFIGURE A MORE SECURED ENCRYPTED PASSWORD
  SW1(config)#enable secret CCNA12(password)

- SAVE THE RUNNING-CONFIG TO STARTUP-CONFIG
  SW1#write
  or
  SW1#write memory
  or
  SW1#copy running-config startup-config
